JCuganda

What is JCuganda?
JCuganda (Job Creators Uganda) is a dream of Mr. Katemba Julius who is a vision bearer and its founder member as well.

Back ground:
The commercialization of Education, Education systems, (Education that trains into becoming job seekers other than becoming job creators) and low levels of Industrialization in Uganda and East Africa as whole has resulted into un employment problem to the majority of the people in the area, greatly the youth.

Community and family systems break down as there is need for feeding, clothing, Accommodation, Health, Education Etc  and as result cases like Murder, Theft, Prostitution, Robbery, and other related cases have merged in order to meet  the above necessities of life.

It is for these devastating effects of un-employment on the communities and Families of Uganda that led the managing Director and Founder member as well, Mr. Katemba Julius to design ways and approaches in 2008 for the reduction/ eradication of poverty through collective efforts of JCuganda.

JCuganda started its operations in January 2009 in Uganda. Currently it is being carried out in Kabale District and intending to take to other parts of the Country and Africa as whole.

Mission:
To promote Social-Economic activities among the communities of Uganda and Africa at large through involvement in income generating projects like; Poultry, Piggery, Bee keeping, Rabbit rearing, Zero Grazing of cattle, Small scale retail business, and other Business ventures, to reduce/ eradicate effects of un-employment in Uganda  and Africa as whole.
Aims and objectives:
 To promote a culture of being job creators other than job seekers to the JCuganda members through skills training in local micro entrepreneurs in order to enhance their competitiveness in quality production and profitability, Create, enhance and encourage income generating projects to members of JCuganda and promote the welfare for a better future.

 To market the products of JCuganda members through established business centers in major Towns of  Uganda, Towns in bordering Countries like, Rwanda, Democratic Republic of Congo, Tanzania, Kenya, Sudan, and other countries in and out side Africa.

 To promote and carry out block purchases of Raw materials/ products for micro and small scale entrepreneurs of JCuganda in order to low the costs of materials for production/ sales.

 To promote and encourage study courses that lead to job creation, self employment that under going for courses that lead to white color jobs only.

 To encourage self reliance of individual members of JCuganda through provision of advisory services on how to make savings.

 To promote the welfare and the development of small, medium, and large projects of members of JCuganda by giving relevant skills training programs through regular up grading and refresher courses.

 To promote the economic self reliance of individual members by extending soft loans as micro-credit scheme and encourage income generating activities to communities and Families of Uganda and improve on their standards of living.

 Promote carrier guidance to the students from primary level to the higher institutions of learning that have a multiple of job opportunities to increase on chances of getting jobs.

 To mobilize funds for the youth at different levels of education that can help them attain their education or complete their studies and help those who will have already finished their studies to start their self income generating projects.

 To help Business community by giving them Training courses on Business management/ Record Keeping.

 To make JCuganda a source or provider of man powers to the employers (investors) in various field.

 To educate and provide counseling services to the masses on the dangers and effects of HIV/ AIDS and other STDs that may be got from prostitution of which many people have taken as their sources of their income.

 To develop the entire Nation(s) Economically, Socially, Religiously, and politically as one community.
